cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "hyperspace: Cross-Model Evolution of Self-Modifying Code"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
version: 0.1.1
date-released: 2026-04-09
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.19488272
url: https://github.com/opinionated-systems/hyperspace
abstract: >
  LLM agents on different models evolve both their task code and the
  code that decides how to improve, then discover and adopt each
  other's strategies without being told to cooperate. The agents span
  proprietary and open-weight models across capability tiers. Safety
  is enforced at the infrastructure level via markspace, outside the
  agent's editable scope. Includes a faithful replication of
  Hyperagents DGM-H (Zhang et al., 2026) on IMO-GradingBench and
  cross-model transfer experiments across 5 model pairings with 30
  voluntary adoption events backed by LLM trace evidence.
